channel_description: Take one more step up the ladder by joining Ash in the Johto region in Pokémon: The Johto Journeys, now on Pokémon TV!

media.description: Ash begins his journey in Johto, a largely unexplored region said to be thickly populated with Pokémon entirely new to him and his friends.
media.title: Don't Touch That 'dile

media.description: In a Pokémon battle, Ash soundly defeats an ambitious young Trainer, who runs away dejectedly.
media.title: The Double Trouble Header

media.description: Ash and friends discover a forest where invading Pinsir are causing heavy deforestation.
media.title: A Sappy Ending

media.description: Ash and friends stumble into a small valley where Donphan are used to harvest precious stones.
media.title: Roll On, Pokémon!

media.description: Who would be foolish enough to brave a thick forest in the dead of night without a Hoothoot guide? Certainly not Ash Ketchum...
media.title: Illusion Confusion

media.description: Our heroes must help prepare an insecure Bellossom dance troupe for their upcoming exhibition.
media.title: Flower Power

media.description: Ash and friends reach a new town and hear of three mysterious robbers apparently mimicking the crimes of a legendary master thief.
media.title: Spinarak Attack

media.description: With pet food prepared by a French chef, rooms of WalkMaster exercise equipment and closets stocked with the latest in Pokémon fashion, life couldn't be much better for a Palm Hills Snubbull.
media.title: Snubbull Snobbery

media.description: Brock saves a lost and frightened Stantler fawn and carefully nurses it back to health before releasing it.
media.title: The Little Big Horn

media.description: Ash encounters a wild Chikorita and engages it in battle, thinking to add it to his team.
media.title: Chikorita Rescue

media.description: Professor Oak's errand—to deliver the mysterious GS Ball to a Poké Ball expert—is interrupted when a Quagsire with a penchant for spherical objects steals the GS ball for use in a nocturnal ritual.
media.title: Once in a Blue Moon

media.description: When Team Rocket attacks Ash and his friends, a brave young Trainer and her flock of Ledyba come to the rescue.
media.title: The Whistle Stop

media.description: Team Rocket can't believe their luck when the Blissey employed in a Pokémon Center willingly gives them the cente's entire food supply.
media.title: Ignorance Is Blissey

media.description: Our heroes are recruited as guest instructors at a youth Pokémon Academy.
media.title: A Bout With Sprout

media.description: With Pikachu's help, Ash is confident that winning the Zephyr badge will be a breeze.
media.title: Fighting Flyer with Fire

media.description: Cute and cuddly is one thing, but a bawling Marill is too much even for Misty.
media.title: For Crying Out Loud

media.description: Team Rocket's most recent super vehicle, the Arbotank, is their ticket to world domination.
media.title: Tanks A Lot!

media.description: When Ash hears of the nearby Charicific Valley, he is sure a quick trip would be just the thing to reignite his Charizard's flagging spirits.
media.title: Charizard's Burning Ambition

media.description: The annual Sunflora contest is only a day away and yet our hero's new friend and Sunflora Trainer is unable to convince her star Pokémon to compete.
media.title: Grin to Win!

media.description: A severe case of rivalry between Pikachu and Chikorita calls for therapy sessions with Nurse Joy.
media.title: Chikorita's Big Upset

media.description: Our heroes chance upon a Hoppip—the fluffy ''Cottonweed'' Pokémon that is able to drift for miles on a passing wind.
media.title: Foul Weather Friends

media.description: When Ash and friends wander into town, they bring with them a challenge that threatens to be Gligarman's last—Team Rocket.
media.title: The Superhero Secret

media.description: Team Rocket comes in sheep's clothing to relieve a kind Poké-shepherd of her Mareep flock.
media.title: Mild 'N Wooly

media.description: When the most promising trainee at a Pokémon dojo abandons battle altogether, it's up to Ash and friends to convince him that battling is more than just a matter of probability.
media.title: Wired For Battle

media.description: With Charizard gone and no fire Pokémon to call his own, Ash is overjoyed to come across a Cyndaquil in the wild.
media.title: Good 'Quil Hunting

media.description: Ash carelessly makes enemies of the Slowpoke-worshipping residents of a town.
media.title: A Shadow of a Drought

media.description: Ash delivers the mysterious GS Ball to a renowned Pokémon expert, but Team Rocket wreaks trouble when they attempt to harvest the Apricorns essential to local Poké Ball production.
media.title: Going Apricorn

media.description: When Ash reaches the Hive Gym, he has just the Pokémon to challenge the Gym Leader's Bug Pokémon.
media.title: Gettin' the Bugs Out

media.description: An inexperienced young Trainer mistakenly scares off his own Farfetch'd.
media.title: A Farfetch'd Tale

media.description: At the Pokémon Swap Meet, our heroes befriend a young Pokémon trainer who's having difficulties finding a trading partner willing to accept his Wobbuffet. When Jessie inadvertently deposits her Poké Ball across from his in the exchanger, this young trainer gets more than he had bargained for.
media.title: Tricks of the Trade

media.description: An unexpected Pokémon firefighting competition reunites our heroes with some old friends, the Squirtle Squad! But they are in desperate need of some leadership, so Ash and Squirtle rejoin the ranks.
media.title: The Fire-ing Squad!

media.description: When they stumble upon a preschool for Wooper and an emergency calls the teacher away, our heroes come to the rescue! But, as always, Team Rocket is around the corner and up to no good…
media.title: No Big Woop!

media.description: While Ash and friends deliberate on how to pass through a tunnel replete with Onix, two wandering Pokémon arrive on the scene together.
media.title: Tunnel Vision

media.description: Investigating a string of mysterious thefts, our heroes discover a pack of Houndour, struggling to survive in the wild.
media.title: Hour of the Houndour

media.description: Ash and Misty's friendly rivalry is tested when they both try to capture a Totodile at the same time. Unable to determine whose Poké Ball had captured the wild Pokémon, the two must battle it out to determine the Totodile's new master.
media.title: The Totodile Duel

media.description: When Ash and friends hear of a virtually undefeatable trainer operating nearby, they seek her out.
media.title: Hot Matches

media.description: Ash's Totodile falls head over tail for a passing Azumarill, but is still unsuccessful in having its feelings requited when Team Rocket kidnap the Pokémon before Totodile's eyes.
media.title: Love, Totodile Style

media.description: Ash has his sights set on a rare and brightly-colored Noctowl.
media.title: Fowl Play

media.description: When an Ursaring attack leaves Team Rocket and our heroes in compromising positions, compromise they do, members of each team being paired with members of the other.
media.title: Forest Grumps

media.description: Our heroes come to a town whose residents all raise Psychic Pokémon to repel the Ghost Pokémon that lurk nearby
media.title: The Psychic Sidekicks

media.description: A Pokémon Fortune Telling boom turns out to be a Team Rocket plot to steal Pokémon from local trainers.
media.title: The Fortune Hunters
